    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><h2>Problem Statement</h2>\n<p>We have <b>N</b> people standing of one side of river and only one boat to cross the river. The rowing time of all the persons is given. A boat can accomodate maximum 2 people at a time and the time of rowing is same is the time of rowing of slower person. Find the minimum total time in which all persons can cross the river.</p>\n\n<p><b>Note that people whose rowing time is less are given by larger integers.</b></p>\n\n<h3>Input section</h3>\n<p>The first line contains, <b>T</b>, denoting the number of test cases.</p>\n\n<p>Each test case contains 2 lines each. The first line has an integer <b>N</b>, denoting the number of persons. Next line contains <b>N</b> space separated <b>distinct</b> integers denoting the rowing time of people.</p>\n\n<h3>Output section</h3>\n<p>For each test case, print the minimum time required to cross the people.</p>\n\n<h3>Input constraints</h3>\n<pre>\n1 \u2264 T \u2264 10\n1 \u2264 N \u2264 20\n1 \u2264 A[i] \u2264 100000, A[i] is the array of rowing time\n</pre>\n\n<h3>Subtasks</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Subtask <b>#1</b> (10 points) : 1 \u2264 T \u2264 10, 1 \u2264 N \u2264 3</li>\n<li>Subtask <b>#2</b> (20 points) : 1 \u2264 T \u2264 5, 1 \u2264 N \u2264 8</li>\n<li>Subtask <b>#3</b> (30 points) : 1 \u2264 T \u2264 5, 1 \u2264 N \u2264 10</li>\n<li>Subtask <b>#4</b> (40 points) : 1 \u2264 T \u2264 3, 1 \u2264 N \u2264 20</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Sample Input</h3>\n<pre>\n3\n2\n200 100\n3\n100 200 300\n4\n623 821 145 720\n</pre>\n\n<h3>Sample Output</h3>\n<pre>\n200\n600\n2454\n\n</pre>\n\n<p>For the second test case, the required moves are : </p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Send person 1 and 2 in the boat. The rowing time will be 200.</li>\n<li>Let the person 1 come back. The rowing time will be 100.</li>\n<li>Send the person 1 and 3 in the boat. The rowing time will be 300.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p></p>\n<p>Hence the total time taken is (200 + 100 + 300) = 600</p>",
